SIMPLE: snap_shot
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Snap shot
<hw>Snap shot</hw>.</altsp> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A quick
offhand shot, made without deliberately taking aim over the
sights.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Photog.)</fld> <def>Act of taking a
snapshot (in sense 2).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An instantaneous photograph made, usually with a
hand camera, without formal posing of, and often without the
foreknowledge of, the subject.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>a brief summary or appraisal, especially one that
describes the state of a situation at one particular time; <as>as, a
<ex>snapshot</ex> of the moon project in 1966</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snapweed</ent>⟦br⟧
